1
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:18,625
[NARRATOR]
Light and darkness...

2
00:00:18,708 --> 00:00:22,625
The final battle of the gods
climaxed in a clash between

3
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:25,750
Marfa, goddess of all creation,

4
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:29,583
and Kardis,
goddess of destruction.

5
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:31,625
At the end of their
fierce battle,

6
00:00:31,708 --> 00:00:34,750
the stricken goddesses
had split the continent,

7
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:37,041
forming a new land.

8
00:00:37,125 --> 00:00:41,416
Since then, people have come
to call this new continent

9
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,291
"Lodoss - The Accursed Island."

10
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,750
<i>The way that you</i>

11
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:05,166
<i>embrace me with your</i>
<i>strong and powerful arms</i>

12
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:13,083
<i>Your haunting words keep me</i>
<i>close to everything about you</i>

13
00:01:14,458 --> 00:01:17,541
<i>Romantic in ways</i>

14
00:01:17,625 --> 00:01:21,958
<i>in ways that almost</i>
<i>tear upon my heart</i>

15
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:24,416
<i>Can't let you go</i>

16
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,666
<i>Don't you know?</i>

17
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:32,083
<i>Io sono prigioniera</i>

18
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:36,375
<i>A captive in</i>
<i>your gentle hands</i>

19
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:39,500
<i>A prisoner of</i>
<i>your soulful eyes,</i>

20
00:01:39,583 --> 00:01:44,458
<i>your special smile</i>
<i>will never part</i>

21
00:01:44,541 --> 00:01:48,875
<i>If the morning sun</i>
<i>should free me</i>

22
00:01:48,958 --> 00:01:53,083
<i>It really wouldn't let me go</i>

23
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:56,291
<i>I'd still be caught</i>
<i>inside your love</i>

24
00:01:56,375 --> 00:01:58,375
<i>Can't rise above</i>

25
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:05,291
<i>the chains of your heart</i>

26
00:02:15,291 --> 00:02:23,958
[birds chirping]

27
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:50,000
[NEESE]
You're really going?

28
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:54,583
I am. And I'm
coming back with her.

29
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:56,583
[NEESE]
Is it still possible?

30
00:02:56,666 --> 00:02:58,250
It's been such a long time--

31
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,875
[GHIM]
Neese!

32
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:02,541
You're not just a priestess.
You're a mother.

33
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:06,958
And no parent
should ever give up hope.

34
00:03:07,041 --> 00:03:10,250
Ghim...

35
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,875
Don't worry.
I may be older now,

36
00:03:12,958 --> 00:03:14,708
but I'm still good
enough to bring home

37
00:03:14,791 --> 00:03:16,708
a prodigal
daughter or two.

38
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:21,666
[laughs]

39
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:27,333
Relax!
[laughs]

40
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:38,916
[NEESE] It's almost
as if he blames himself

41
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,458
for Leylia's disappearance.

42
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:45,083
But it's been seven years.

43
00:03:45,166 --> 00:03:48,458
My child... My Leylia...

44
00:03:53,083 --> 00:04:00,083
[DRAGON roars]

45
00:04:00,166 --> 00:04:02,125
[NEESE]
Thank you, Bramd.

46
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:04,833
You fear for her as well.

47
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:17,458
[growls]

48
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:24,500
[roars]

49
00:04:24,583 --> 00:04:27,166
[LIARA gasps]

50
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:30,833
[rustling]

51
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:32,791
[gasps]

52
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:43,291
[whimpers]

53
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:45,083
[gasps]

54
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:46,833
[PARN]
Huh?

55
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:56,041
[LIARA gasps, whimpers]

56
00:05:01,916 --> 00:05:04,333
[GOLBIN roars]

57
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:10,583
[yells]

58
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:12,833
Are you all right there?

59
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:15,000
Parn!

60
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,625
[PARN]
Run!

61
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:28,500
[GOBLIN growls]

62
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:30,583
[PARN groans]

63
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,833
[yells]

64
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:03,625
[pants]

65
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,541
[ETOH] Quite heroic.
Well done, I must say.

66
00:06:09,625 --> 00:06:15,708
But I always thought goblins
were night creatures.

67
00:06:15,791 --> 00:06:17,708
Etoh!

68
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:30,875
[PARN]
Isn't it strange?

69
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,791
After all this time,
now you're taking care of me.

70
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:37,583
As a novitiate of Falis,
I've gained the power to heal.

71
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:38,958
Let's see if I can help.

72
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:40,958
[groans]

73
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:43,791
"O Great Falis,
bring your healing forces

74
00:06:43,875 --> 00:06:46,791
to these wounds..."

75
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:49,041
It should be better, soon.

76
00:06:50,875 --> 00:06:52,958
Ooh.

77
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:57,500
Hey! I shoulda known
it was you!

78
00:06:57,583 --> 00:06:59,250
Zacto!

79
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:00,750
Goblins should be
frightened off,

80
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:02,916
but they should
never be killed!

81
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,666
Parn! Why do you always hafta
make every fight worse?

82
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,083
Aren't you the ones
who are making

83
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:10,541
this needless fight even worse?

84
00:07:10,625 --> 00:07:13,666
So, Etoh,
has it been four years?

85
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:17,291
Well, you don't know how things
have been lately, do you?

86
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:18,791
He's just like his father!

87
00:07:18,875 --> 00:07:20,791
Always going against
the village's decisions

88
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:22,541
without a care in the world!

89
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:24,125
[PARN]
Watch it!

90
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:26,250
Admit it. Your father
broke the kingdom's laws

91
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:31,041
and was cast out from
the Holy Order of Knights.

92
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:34,000
Admit it--
like father, like son.

93
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:35,625
Come here!

94
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,041
[BOTH grunt]

95
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,250
[MAYOR]
Stop it, Parn!

96
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,458
[PARN]
Mayor!

97
00:07:40,541 --> 00:07:43,291
For what it's worth,
I'd like to say thanks.

98
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:46,000
But sir, it was nothing...

99
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:49,291
Thank him? Are you sure you
wanna say that, Mr. Mayor?

100
00:07:49,375 --> 00:07:51,000
After all, wasn't it
you who gave us

101
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:53,125
the order to leave
the goblins alone?

102
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:54,750
Yes, but this is a...

103
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:58,000
They'll be back, all right.
Looking for revenge.

104
00:07:58,083 --> 00:07:59,166
[PARN]
Then I'll just--

105
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:01,166
[VILLAGER B]
Beat 'em all and be a hero?

106
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:04,000
Enough! There's nothing to be
gained by this bickering.

107
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,458
[PARN]
But--!

108
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:07,750
[MAYOR] This is a problem
for the entire village.

109
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,958
We mustn't be rash.

110
00:08:14,083 --> 00:08:17,291
[birds chirping]

111
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:26,166
[GOBLINS growling]

112
00:08:55,166 --> 00:09:02,208
[growling]

113
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:30,583
[fire crackling]

114
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:33,333
[GHIM] Have you got
a cup of that for me?

115
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:48,916
[thunder rumbles]

116
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,541
It's been like that lately.

117
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:53,291
Neese said it herself.

118
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:57,250
Something seems to darken
the spirit of all Lodoss.

119
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:09,625
You can ask all you want,
but I'm not going with you.

120
00:10:09,708 --> 00:10:11,333
Stay in here all day,

121
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:13,916
and those powers of yours
will waste away.

122
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,458
I'm a sorcerer, not a warrior.

123
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:17,791
[GHIM grunts]

124
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:20,291
And my magic isn't
yet what it could be.

125
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:23,958
I've got so much more
material to read up on.

126
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:25,291
[GHIM grunts]

127
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:28,875
What good are books to you?

128
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,458
[knocking]

129
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:31,875
A flood of customers.

130
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:34,333
Must by my busy season.

131
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:39,875
Master Slayn, I need some
advice about the village.

132
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:58,833
[giggles]

133
00:10:58,916 --> 00:11:00,916
[gasps]

134
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:12,166
[DEEDLIT] Goblins?
Out in broad daylight?

135
00:11:28,875 --> 00:11:32,416
[VILLAGER C] Your father was
a Holy Knight of Valis?

136
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,791
[VILLAGER D] Worthy knights
don't die in disgrace,

137
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,750
like he did!

138
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:57,125
[laughs]

139
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:15,083
Pa...pa...

140
00:13:34,291 --> 00:13:36,166
[clink]

141
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,125
[PARN]
Father.

142
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:47,625
[ETOH]
Need a partner?

143
00:13:47,708 --> 00:13:51,333
[PARN]
Huh? Wha--?

144
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:54,375
Shall we be off then,
Sir Knight?

145
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:56,625
Etoh!

146
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:58,083
Think about your future!

147
00:13:58,166 --> 00:13:59,791
You've spent the last
four years of your life

148
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:01,958
studying to be
a priest of Falis!

149
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,333
Please. I'm still
a novice, at best.

150
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:07,583
"Never be so proud that you pass
up a chance for experience."

151
00:14:07,666 --> 00:14:17,625
My teacher's favorite saying.

152
00:14:17,708 --> 00:14:27,666
My teacher's favorite saying.

153
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:34,208
My teacher's favorite saying.

154
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:36,375
[PARN yells]

155
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:44,041
[grunting]

156
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:49,125
[ETOH]
Parn!

157
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:52,083
What the...?!

158
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:53,708
[DEEDLIT]
Try the village.

159
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:55,708
[BOTH]
Huh?

160
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:06,125
[BOTH gasp]

161
00:15:11,166 --> 00:15:13,250
It's an elf!

162
00:15:19,583 --> 00:15:22,708
[PARN gasps] The town
must be under attack!

163
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:27,083
--[GOBLINS growl]
--[screams]

164
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:38,375
[groans]

165
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:41,875
[growls]

166
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:07,500
[growls lowly]

167
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:09,833
[WOMAN gasps]

168
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:19,333
[GHIM growls]

169
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:33,791
What's happened to them?

170
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:36,291
It would appear the goblins
are under a spell.

171
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:37,750
Can you break it?

172
00:16:37,833 --> 00:16:39,791
I can try.

173
00:16:39,875 --> 00:16:42,666
"You, whose spirits
are controlled by evil,

174
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:45,416
set free your hearts
and answer me.

175
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:48,541
You, whose spirits
are controlled by evil,

176
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:52,750
set free your hearts
and answer me.

177
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:56,708
You, whose spirits
are controlled by evil,

178
00:16:56,791 --> 00:17:00,333
set free your hearts
and answer me."

179
00:17:00,416 --> 00:17:08,041
[GOBLINS screeching]

180
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,583
[SLAYN pants]

181
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:16,958
--Are you all right?
--Yes.

182
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:18,958
Heh, you've improved
quite a bit

183
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:20,708
since the last time I saw you.

184
00:17:20,791 --> 00:17:23,708
Liara! Liara!

185
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,833
[screams]

186
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,625
[LIARA]
Parn!

187
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:40,916
Call off your army.
I'm the one

188
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,083
who killed your man.
I'm the one you want!

189
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:44,916
Leave the others out of it!

190
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,500
Quickly! Run!

191
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:59,500
[gulps]

192
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:21,041
[BOTH grunting]

193
00:18:22,708 --> 00:18:26,416
--[LIARA] Father!
--Liara!

194
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:29,250
Father, Parn needs help!

195
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:45,833
[growls, yells]

196
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:50,208
[PARN groans]

197
00:18:57,500 --> 00:19:00,708
[LIARA] Master,
I beg of you! Save him!

198
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:04,416
[PARN groans, yelps]

199
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,750
I'll get you!

200
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:12,708
[yells]

201
00:19:12,791 --> 00:19:15,958
He's an undisciplined young
boy, but there's potential.

202
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:17,875
[GHIM grunts]

203
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:21,833
[PARN groans]

204
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:36,750
[SLAYN] Point your sword
to the heavens.

205
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:46,041
Quickly now! Your sword!

206
00:19:47,875 --> 00:19:49,708
"Creators of all things,

207
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:54,083
grant him the power
to smash this darkness."

208
00:19:54,166 --> 00:19:57,625
[groans]

209
00:19:57,708 --> 00:20:00,125
[PARN yells]

210
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,125
[pants]

211
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:07,083
[ETOH]
Parn!

212
00:20:16,625 --> 00:20:17,666
[VILLAGERS chattering]

213
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,166
[VILLAGER E]
It's all Parn's fault!

214
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:20,916
He's the reason
we were attacked!

215
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,625
[VILLAGER F]
Yeah! I say we banish him!

216
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:25,791
[VILLAGER G]
But after what he did!

217
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,208
[VILLAGER H]
If we're too easy on him,

218
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:29,083
it'll just happen again!

219
00:20:29,166 --> 00:20:35,750
[chattering continues]

220
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:37,958
Although we can't explain it,

221
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:42,666
some dark evil is
awakening across Lodoss.

222
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,125
[MAYOR]
If we stay here,

223
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,000
we won't know
anything for sure.

224
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:54,833
Therefore, I have decided to

225
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:58,500
send Parn out to
investigate the situation.

226
00:20:58,583 --> 00:20:59,916
[chattering]

227
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,958
[LIARA sighs]

228
00:22:19,625 --> 00:22:21,458
[PARN]
Huh?

229
00:22:21,541 --> 00:22:25,250
Hey, Parn! Looks like our
adventure's just starting up.

230
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:27,291
[GHIM] Well, it seems
to me that you kids

231
00:22:27,375 --> 00:22:29,708
may need some help
from here on in.

232
00:22:29,791 --> 00:22:31,541
[PARN]
Huh?

233
00:22:31,625 --> 00:22:36,541
Dunno why, but even lead-footed
Slayn here has offered to come.

234
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:49,458
[NARRATOR] Hearts
following separate paths

235
00:22:49,541 --> 00:22:51,416
gather into one light,

236
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:53,958
and now,
set off for the future.

237
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:57,000
But they still know not
of the darkness that lies

238
00:22:57,083 --> 00:23:01,000
sleeping in the
lowest depths of Lodoss.

239
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:12,250
<i>Let all the wonders</i>
<i>come to me</i>

240
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:16,791
<i>The fantasy fills,</i>
<i>fills my heart</i>

241
00:23:16,875 --> 00:23:20,833
<i>I'll never wander anymore</i>

242
00:23:20,916 --> 00:23:24,166
<i>For all the love I have,</i>
<i>I have for you</i>

243
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:28,791
<i>All the spirits of the wind</i>

244
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:32,625
<i>Spread their magic</i>
<i>wings and fly</i>

245
00:23:32,708 --> 00:23:37,333
<i>Racing at the speed of light</i>

246
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:44,208
<i>Through the valleys</i>
<i>and the passages of time</i>

247
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:46,291
<i>When we fell in love</i>

248
00:23:46,375 --> 00:23:48,166
<i>Destiny</i>

249
00:23:48,250 --> 00:23:50,208
<i>Now each night</i>
<i>will have no end</i>

250
00:23:50,291 --> 00:23:52,458
<i>Our nights will never end</i>

251
00:23:52,541 --> 00:23:54,833
<i>Eternity awaits</i>

252
00:23:54,916 --> 00:23:56,833
<i>You and me</i>

253
00:23:56,916 --> 00:24:03,250
<i>Now that you are here</i>

